<title>UK: RJB says miners decide not to buy Welsh pit.</title>
<headline>RJB says miners decide not to buy Welsh pit.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-08-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>RJB Mining Plc said on Friday that miners at Point of Ayr in north Wales have decided not to make a buy-out offer for the loss-making pit which will be closed tonight.</p>
<p>An RJB spokesman told Reuters miners had made the decision one hour ago. Miners' trade union representatives had approached the company about a possible deal but subsequently learned of the extent of losses from the mine.</p>
<p>Losses totalled five million stg since the mine was bought from British Coal 19 months ago. Point of Ayr is the last deep coal mine in north Wales.</p>
</text>
